Fold build context path into the image tag

The devcontainer image tag hashed the Dockerfile and tracked context
content but deliberately ignored both `.git` and the context's
filesystem path.  In tests every repo produces byte-identical tracked
content, so they all collapsed onto one cached image tag; whichever
test built first won the cache, and a stray local branch baked into
that image (via `COPY . `, since `.git` is excluded from the hash but
not from the build) leaked into every pod that reused it, breaking
isolation.

Thread a `ContextPathTagging` choice through `resolve_image` and fold
the context path into the tag for every real context (the repo root,
stable across runs).  Distinct repos now get distinct images, so test
pods can no longer share one.  The built-in default image keeps the
old path-agnostic tag because it is staged into a tempdir that moves
on every invocation; including its path would defeat the cache.

This also isolates the prepared image, whose tag derives from the base
image tag, so no per-test normalization of the baked `.git` is needed.
